1
00:00:11,020 --> 00:00:16,970
[Fenglinwan Hotel]

2
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:45,000
Qiqi,

3
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:46,520
I'm sorry.

4
00:00:47,840 --> 00:00:49,640
It's the same old problem again.

5
00:01:00,390 --> 00:01:01,110
It's okay.

6
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:02,830
I can wait.

7
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:08,930
Ms. Zhou.

8
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:11,230
They're all waiting for you
to start the meeting.

9
00:01:11,230 --> 00:01:12,200
Let them wait.

10
00:01:12,350 --> 00:01:13,550
How long will that be?

11
00:01:16,470 --> 00:01:18,130
Wait until the cows come home.

12
00:02:38,550 --> 00:02:42,260
[Born with Luck]

13
00:02:42,310 --> 00:02:45,300
[Episode 7]

14
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:46,560
What a windfall.

15
00:02:47,470 --> 00:02:48,560
Now I finally get

16
00:02:48,590 --> 00:02:50,360
why you kept provoking the bear.

17
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:52,710
Turns out,
you had everything under control.

18
00:02:52,710 --> 00:02:54,030
I was just playing it by ear.

19
00:02:54,030 --> 00:02:55,430
Sometimes, you've got to improvise.

20
00:02:55,430 --> 00:02:56,520
Don't be so modest.

21
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:57,870
If you'd told me earlier we were
doing a straight-man-funny-man act,

22
00:02:57,870 --> 00:02:58,890
I could've played along
even better.

23
00:02:58,890 --> 00:03:00,290
Alright, next time then.

24
00:03:01,030 --> 00:03:01,870
We tracked down the whistleblower

25
00:03:01,870 --> 00:03:03,190
this fast—

26
00:03:03,310 --> 00:03:05,590
honestly, I still can't quite believe it.

27
00:03:05,590 --> 00:03:07,310
No wonder Chief Zhang said before

28
00:03:07,310 --> 00:03:08,960
that if we want
to investigate Lu Zheng's case,

29
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:10,870
we have to start
with Ye Jian's case first.

30
00:03:10,870 --> 00:03:13,000
That foresight is really incredible.

31
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,160
Every case must

32
00:03:16,190 --> 00:03:17,310
have a crack somewhere.

33
00:03:17,310 --> 00:03:18,120
We just have to find it.

34
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:19,980
As we keep looking, we'll find it.

35
00:03:20,750 --> 00:03:22,560
But Lu Yibo still refuses to say

36
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:23,680
who exactly he reported.

37
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:24,630
So Chief Lu's case

38
00:03:24,630 --> 00:03:26,160
still lacks hard evidence.

39
00:03:26,590 --> 00:03:27,560
Sometimes saying nothing

40
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:29,240
speaks louder than anything.

41
00:03:33,079 --> 00:03:34,410
You reported Zhou Rong?

42
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,850
Have you lost your mind?

43
00:03:36,079 --> 00:03:37,030
Six months ago,

44
00:03:37,079 --> 00:03:38,210
a police chief died.

45
00:03:38,870 --> 00:03:39,560
I had a feeling that

46
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:41,030
it had something to do with Mr. Rong.

47
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:42,560
So I wrote the report letter.

48
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:43,520
Why?

49
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:44,079
Why?

50
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:45,400
Because I love you.

51
00:03:52,910 --> 00:03:54,310
Because of my own issues.

52
00:03:54,910 --> 00:03:56,110
I started suspecting

53
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:57,590
you were lonely

54
00:03:57,590 --> 00:03:58,990
and slept with Zhou Rong.

55
00:04:00,310 --> 00:04:01,750
I suspected you two were having an affair.

56
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:03,430
What nonsense are you talking about?

57
00:04:03,430 --> 00:04:04,080
I'm not that kind

58
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:05,680
of woman with no boundaries!

59
00:04:06,630 --> 00:04:07,660
Qiqi, Qiqi.

60
00:04:07,870 --> 00:04:08,600
I already got

61
00:04:08,630 --> 00:04:09,190
the report letter back.

62
00:04:09,190 --> 00:04:11,390
What's the point of getting it back now?

63
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:13,560
The police have already
shown up at the door.

64
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,470
If Zhou Rong finds out

65
00:04:14,470 --> 00:04:15,360
you were the one who reported him—

66
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:16,560
we're both finished!

67
00:04:19,190 --> 00:04:20,630
You're really that scared of him?

68
00:04:20,630 --> 00:04:22,000
Who do you think Zhou Rong is?

69
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,130
There's nothing that man wouldn't do.

70
00:04:27,830 --> 00:04:29,230
Let me ask you something.

71
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:31,030
Are you with me

72
00:04:31,190 --> 00:04:32,470
because you like me—

73
00:04:34,430 --> 00:04:34,870
or because

74
00:04:34,870 --> 00:04:36,530
I'm Zhou Rong's close friend?

75
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:51,120
I love you.

76
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,460
You're the only one I love.

77
00:04:54,070 --> 00:04:54,950
So we have to

78
00:04:54,950 --> 00:04:56,510
think long-term about this.

79
00:04:56,510 --> 00:04:57,310
Understand?

80
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:00,160
I understand.

81
00:05:00,750 --> 00:05:01,920
So what do we do now?

82
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:17,120
Does Zhou Rong know about your problem?

83
00:05:28,670 --> 00:05:30,330
We need to make the first move.

84
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:45,270
Bro,

85
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:47,720
I've still got some nuts left.

86
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:48,720
Let's split them.

87
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:51,950
I'm not hungry. You can eat them all.

88
00:05:52,159 --> 00:05:52,950
Cut the crap.

89
00:05:53,070 --> 00:05:54,000
Give me your hand.

90
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,600
I'm not the type to hog it all.

91
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:56,080
Hurry.

92
00:06:16,390 --> 00:06:17,430
It smells so good.

93
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,400
Too bad there's barely any left.

94
00:06:24,270 --> 00:06:24,800
Bro,

95
00:06:25,430 --> 00:06:26,690
he still hasn't moved?

96
00:06:33,460 --> 00:06:34,260
Bro, can we...

97
00:06:35,510 --> 00:06:36,440
We can't.

98
00:06:37,310 --> 00:06:38,270
I know you want to leave

99
00:06:38,270 --> 00:06:39,600
and come back tomorrow.

100
00:06:40,190 --> 00:06:41,390
But what if the moment we leave,

101
00:06:41,390 --> 00:06:42,190
he leaves too?

102
00:06:42,830 --> 00:06:43,800
And tomorrow, the second we come back,

103
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:44,800
he comes back too?

104
00:06:45,390 --> 00:06:46,650
What should we do then?

105
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:51,610
It's your turn.

106
00:07:11,950 --> 00:07:12,510
Hello?

107
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:14,540
Director Fang,

108
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:16,680
this is Geng from the radio station.

109
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:18,180
Hello, Director Geng.

110
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:20,610
Director Fang, here's the thing—

111
00:07:21,310 --> 00:07:22,800
that large-scale

112
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:24,430
interactive musical,

113
00:07:24,430 --> 00:07:25,630
and prose poetry recital you planned,

114
00:07:25,630 --> 00:07:27,760
"My Distant Horizon, Your Poetry"...

115
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:30,340
it may need to be postponed.

116
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:30,810
What?

117
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:32,070
No.

118
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:34,750
Why?

119
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:37,430
So when exactly is it airing?

120
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:38,380
Well...

121
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,970
I'm still right here, you know!

122
00:07:45,510 --> 00:07:47,610
You can't treat me like this!

123
00:07:51,570 --> 00:07:52,730
Bro, he moved.

124
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:54,950
Really?

125
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,159
Let's go.

126
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:26,190
Bro.

127
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,240
Shouldn't we wait a little longer?

128
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:30,720
Security's just
a little tighter, that's all.

129
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:32,200
Do you know Warren Buffett?

130
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,909
He makes big money—

131
00:08:34,390 --> 00:08:36,590
money from tens of thousands of people.

132
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:38,510
And he summed it all up in one

133
00:08:38,510 --> 00:08:39,970
valuable piece of advice:

134
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:42,360
"Be fearful when others are greedy,

135
00:08:42,630 --> 00:08:44,690
and greedy when others are fearful."

136
00:08:44,790 --> 00:08:45,650
Think about it—

137
00:08:45,910 --> 00:08:47,440
how many people would actually dare

138
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:49,200
commit a burglary in broad daylight?

139
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,360
When others are fearful—

140
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:52,020
that's our turn to get greedy.

141
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:53,740
Let's do it.

142
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:10,990
In the dark night,

143
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,330
I ride a black horse

144
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:14,490
through thorns and into the darkness.

145
00:09:16,790 --> 00:09:18,240
The moment you wielded your long sword

146
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,390
and slew the dragon—

147
00:09:19,410 --> 00:09:22,140
it made me see the morning glow
for the first time.

148
00:09:29,390 --> 00:09:30,950
[Incoming Call: Mentor]

149
00:09:32,030 --> 00:09:32,550
Mentor.

150
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:33,920
Zhang Yi'ang.

151
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:36,000
How is your investigation going?

152
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:36,720
Ye Jian's case

153
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:37,630
and Lu Zheng's case,

154
00:09:37,630 --> 00:09:38,830
any progress on them?

155
00:09:39,100 --> 00:09:39,900
Yes, there is.

156
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:40,630
But,

157
00:09:40,670 --> 00:09:41,480
on Ye Jian's case,

158
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:42,670
we ran into some obstacles.

159
00:09:42,670 --> 00:09:43,240
So for now,

160
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,900
we're starting with Chief Lu's case.

161
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:45,960
Alright, alright.

162
00:09:46,390 --> 00:09:48,050
I know what you're capable of.

163
00:09:48,550 --> 00:09:49,670
I have some good news.

164
00:09:49,670 --> 00:09:51,070
I have some good news too.

165
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:53,390
Zhang Yi'ang is stepping up.

166
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:53,840
Go ahead.

167
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:55,100
Tell me your good news.

168
00:09:55,670 --> 00:09:56,790
We found the whistleblower.

169
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:57,320
Who is it?

170
00:09:57,790 --> 00:09:58,320
Lu Yibo.

171
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:00,600
Well done.

172
00:10:02,510 --> 00:10:04,030
The Provincial Department
just confirmed it too—

173
00:10:04,030 --> 00:10:05,090
the whistleblower

174
00:10:06,030 --> 00:10:06,970
was indeed Lu Yibo.

175
00:10:06,970 --> 00:10:08,430
See, it really was Lu Yibo.

176
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:09,520
Zhang Yi'ang,

177
00:10:09,630 --> 00:10:10,630
follow this lead

178
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:11,630
and keep digging.

179
00:10:11,630 --> 00:10:13,390
The truth is about to surface.

180
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:14,440
Mentor, rest assured.

181
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:15,170
Understood.

182
00:10:34,630 --> 00:10:35,160
Mr. Rong.

183
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:37,250
Mr. Rong.

184
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:42,790
Plan A:

185
00:10:43,550 --> 00:10:45,200
Fang Yong once published
a poetry collection,

186
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:46,960
and it's impossible to find it elsewhere.

187
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:47,910
The only copy left is an archive edition

188
00:10:47,530 --> 00:10:47,800
[My Distant Horizon, Your Poetry]

189
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:48,950
at the city library.

190
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:49,050
[Fang Yong]

191
00:10:49,150 --> 00:10:50,670
I had someone make a replica.

192
00:10:50,670 --> 00:10:51,670
You can take it to him

193
00:10:51,670 --> 00:10:52,750
and ask him to sign it—

194
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:53,410
it'd also be

195
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:54,720
a good chance to get closer to him.

196
00:10:54,450 --> 00:10:54,750
[Index]

197
00:10:57,630 --> 00:10:59,270
Isn't that basically piracy?

198
00:10:59,270 --> 00:10:59,860
Is it?

199
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:03,000
You want me to walk up to the author

200
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,080
with a pirated copy
and ask for his signature?

201
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:07,000
How exactly am I supposed
to get close to him like that?

202
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,000
My apologies, I didn't think it through.

203
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:09,950
Plan B:

204
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:11,750
I was going to name our company's

205
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:13,210
next residential project

206
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:14,970
as "Yong Residence."

207
00:11:15,270 --> 00:11:17,150
Then we can invite Fang Yong
to cut the ribbon.

208
00:11:17,150 --> 00:11:18,150
What do you think?

209
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:21,950
Yong Residence...

210
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:23,030
Mediocre (Yong) Residence?

211
00:11:23,030 --> 00:11:25,690
Does that mean
only mediocre people live there?

212
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:28,120
Sorry, I didn't think
that one through either.

213
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:29,320
How about this—we find a park

214
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:30,150
and build a life-size bronze statue

215
00:11:30,150 --> 00:11:31,200
of Fang Yong?

216
00:11:31,270 --> 00:11:32,200
That man is alive and perfectly well.

217
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,440
Why on earth would you
build a statue for him?

218
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:34,650
Isn't that a bit over the top?

219
00:11:34,650 --> 00:11:36,580
-Sir. Sir.
-Let's find another...

220
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:37,440
Mr. Zhou.

221
00:11:37,630 --> 00:11:39,150
This gentleman insisted on seeing you.

222
00:11:39,150 --> 00:11:39,720
I couldn't stop him.

223
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:40,250
Mr. Fang.

224
00:11:46,870 --> 00:11:48,120
[My Distant Horizon, Your Poetry]

225
00:11:50,330 --> 00:11:50,890
[My Distant Horizon, Your Poetry]

226
00:12:06,290 --> 00:12:08,690
This copy's printed
way better than my own.

227
00:12:09,170 --> 00:12:10,150
Can I have it?

228
00:12:15,610 --> 00:12:16,320
[My Distant Horizon, Your Poetry]

229
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:16,750
Mr. Fang.

230
00:12:17,330 --> 00:12:19,280
This is just a sample, actually.

231
00:12:19,420 --> 00:12:19,910
We were planning

232
00:12:19,910 --> 00:12:20,840
to make a gold-foil edition

233
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:22,770
and have it delivered to your home.

234
00:12:22,870 --> 00:12:23,760
Your writing

235
00:12:23,870 --> 00:12:24,530
is profound

236
00:12:24,650 --> 00:12:26,600
and brings readers a rare sense of peace.

237
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:28,150
To be honest, just now...

238
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:31,750
I finished reading it
while lying on the floor.

239
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:33,000
If you don't mind,

240
00:12:33,330 --> 00:12:34,200
please accept it.

241
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:37,790
[My Distant Horizon, Your Poetry]

242
00:12:35,390 --> 00:12:35,960
Great.

243
00:12:40,550 --> 00:12:42,280
I'd love to have a chat with you.

244
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:44,500
All this effort you've put in—

245
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:47,180
isn't it just to talk to me?

246
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,000
Sure.

247
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:48,840
Let's talk.

248
00:12:51,870 --> 00:12:53,000
Let's go to my place.

249
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:54,930
Can't we just talk here?

250
00:12:55,550 --> 00:12:57,150
I have something to show you.

251
00:13:04,020 --> 00:13:06,600
♪ Bunny, bunny, bunny, bunny,
bunny, bunny ♪

252
00:13:07,530 --> 00:13:08,790
♪ Love you, love you, love you ♪

253
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:12,750
♪ Bunny, bunny, bunny, bunny,
bunny, bunny ♪

254
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:15,050
♪ Love you, love you, love you ♪

255
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:17,110
♪ Oh Gimme ♪

256
00:13:18,290 --> 00:13:20,170
♪ Dance me in the richness ♪

257
00:13:21,150 --> 00:13:22,820
♪ Raining make it rain ♪

258
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:26,050
♪ Oh cash is my revolution ♪

259
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:31,710
♪ Get your head in the game,
we're all smart people here ♪

260
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:34,930
♪ Don't drag your feet,
even gold slips through slow hands ♪

261
00:13:35,730 --> 00:13:37,340
♪ I beat it, I beat it ♪

262
00:13:38,140 --> 00:13:40,060
♪ Aye aye aye aye yo ♪

263
00:13:44,020 --> 00:13:46,600
♪ Bunny, bunny, bunny, bunny,
bunny, bunny ♪

264
00:13:47,530 --> 00:13:48,790
♪ Love you, love you, love you ♪

265
00:13:50,150 --> 00:13:52,720
♪ Bunny, bunny, bunny, bunny,
bunny, bunny ♪

266
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:55,050
♪ Love you, love you, love you ♪

267
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:00,670
Bro.

268
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:07,770
Don't step on the floor.

269
00:14:11,750 --> 00:14:12,270
Bro.

270
00:14:13,390 --> 00:14:14,600
Are you looking for a corrupt official

271
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:15,730
or a poor household?

272
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:20,480
It's a disguise.

273
00:14:21,790 --> 00:14:25,050
The bigger the corrupt official,
the better the disguise.

274
00:14:25,550 --> 00:14:26,440
He can't just leave his money

275
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:27,900
out in plain sight, can he?

276
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:32,780
If he did, he'd have been reported
a long time ago

277
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,220
I bet one of these rooms

278
00:14:35,270 --> 00:14:36,400
is packed with cash.

279
00:14:37,870 --> 00:14:39,000
Search thoroughly.

280
00:14:39,390 --> 00:14:40,790
Especially the ceiling,

281
00:14:40,790 --> 00:14:41,920
under the mattress,

282
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:44,690
and the hidden compartments in the walls.

283
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:47,190
Don't miss a single spot.

284
